      <hedline>
        <hl1>Frustrated Customers</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Malcolm Campbell letter on July 20 article on the poor quality of customer service in high-tech retailing</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I'm an over 70 nerd who bought his first computer last year from Hewlett-Packard.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I'm an over 70 nerd who bought his first computer last year from Hewlett-Packard.</p>
        <p>Maybe because I didn't know that customer service wasn't as good as it used to be, I told many people about the very helpful technicians who held my hand while I was learning. Early this year the serial port stopped responding to my digital camera, and they led me through the steps to get it working again.</p>
        <p>MALCOLM CAMPBELL  Vineyard Haven, Mass.</p>
      </block>
